TO: REGIONAL DIRECTORS, COMMERCIAL OPERATIONS
DISTRICT DIRECTORS, AREA AND PORT DIRECTORS
FROM: DIRECTOR, IMPORT SPECIALIST DIVISION
RE: PRELIMINARY DETERMINATION OF SALES AT  LESS THAN  FAIR VALUE:
URANIUM FROM KAZAKHSTAN, KYRGYZSTAN, RUSSIA, TAJIKISTAN, UKRAINE,
AND UZBEKISTAN; AND PRELIMINARY DETERMINATIONS OF  SALES  AT  NOT
LESS   THAN   FAIR  VALUE:   URANIUM  FROM  ARMENIA,  AZERBAIJAN,
BYELARUS, GEORGIA, MOLDOVA, AND TURKMENISTAN
1.  THE DEPARTMENT OF  COMMERCE  WILL PUBLISHED  IN  THE  FEDERAL
REGISTER ON JUNE 3, 1992, NOTICE OF ITS PRELIMINARY DETERMINATION
OF  SALES  AT   LESS  THAN  FAIR  VALUE  REGARDING  URANIUM  FROM
KAZAKHSTAN,  KYRGYZSTAN,   RUSSIA,   TAJIKISTAN,   UKRAINE,   AND
Message Date: 06/04/1992         Message Number: 2156114         Page 2 of 5
UZBEKISTAN; AND NOTICE OF  ITS PRELIMINARY DETERMINATION OF SALES
AT  NOT  LESS  THAN  FAIR  VALUE REGARDING URANIUM  FROM ARMENIA,
AZERBAIJAN, BYELARUS, GEORGIA, MOLDOVA, AND TURKMENISTAN.
2.  THE PRODUCTS COVERED BY  THESE INVESTIGATIONS INCLUDE NATURAL
URANIUM IN  THE  FORM  OF URANIUM ORES  AND CONCENTRATES; NATURAL
URANIUM METAL  AND NATURAL URANIUM COMPOUNDS; ALLOYS, DISPERSIONS
(INCLUDING CERMETS),  CERAMIC  PRODUCTS  AND  MIXTURES CONTAINING
NATURAL URANIUM OR NATURAL URANIUM COMPOUNDS; URANIUM ENRICHED IN
U235 AND  ITS COMPOUNDS; ALLOYS, DISPERSIONS (INCLUDING CERMETS),
CERAMIC PRODUCTS,  AND  MIXTURES CONTAINING URANIUM  ENRICHED  IN
U235  OR COMPOUNDS OF URANIUM ENRICHED IN  U235.  HIGHLY ENRICHED
URANIUM, WHICH IS URANIUM ENRICHED TO  A U235 CONCENTRATION LEVEL
AT  OR  ABOVE  20 PERCENT, IS EXCLUDED FROM  THE SCOPE  OF  THESE
INVESTIGATIONS. THE  URANIUM SUBJECT  TO  THESE INVESTIGATIONS IS
PROVIDED  FOR  UNDER  SUBHEADINGS  2612.10.00.00,  2844.10.10.00,
2844.20.00.50, OF THE HARMONIZED TARIFF SCHEDULE (HTS).  ALTHOUGH
THE HTS SUBHEADINGS ARE PROVIDED FOR CONVENIENCE AND CUSTOMS
PURPOSES,  THE  WRITTEN  DESCRIPTION  OF   THE  SCOPE  OF   THESE
PROCEEDINGS IS DISPOSITIVE.
3.  THE  U.S.  CUSTOMS SERVICE SHALL  SUSPEND LIQUIDATION OF  ALL
ENTRIES   OF   URANIUM   FROM   KAZAKHSTAN,  KYRGYZSTAN,  RUSSIA,
TAJIKISTAN, UKRAINE AND UZBEKISTAN THAT ARE ENTERED, OR WITHDRAWN
FROM WAREHOUSE, FOR CONSUMPTION ON  OR AFTER MARCH 5, 1992, WHICH
IS 90 DAYS PRIOR TO THE DATE OF PUBLICATION OF THIS NOTICE IN THE
FEDERAL  REGISTER   DUE   TO   THE  DETERMINATION  THAT  CRITICAL
CIRCUMSTANCES EXIST.   THE  U.S. CUSTOMS SERVICE SHALL REQUIRE  A
CASH DEPOSIT OR  THE POSTING OF  A  BOND EQUAL TO 115.82 PERCENT.
DUE TO  THE DEPARTMENT'S PRELIMINARY NEGATIVE DETERMINATIONS WITH
RESPECT  TO ARMENIA, AZERBAIJAN, BYELARUS, GEORGIA, MOLDOVA,  AND
TURKMENISTAN, CUSTOMS SHALL NOT SUSPEND LIQUIDATION OF ENTRIES OF
URANIUM FROM THESE COUNTRIES.
4.  FOR INVESTIGATION PURPOSES ONLY, THESE ANTIDUMPING DUTY CASES
Message Date: 06/04/1992         Message Number: 2156114         Page 3 of 5
HAVE   BEEN   ASSIGNED   THE   FOLLOWING  INVESTIGATION  NUMBERS:
A-843-802, WHICH CORRESPOND TO EACH COUNTRY IN  THE ORDER EACH IS
LISTED IN THE TITLE ABOVE.
5.  FOR CUSTOMS REPORTING PURPOSES, PLEASE USE THE FOLLOWING CASE
NUMBERS:
RUSSIA             A-462-102
BELARUS            A-462-202
UKRAINE            A-462-302
ARMENIA            A-463-102
AZERBAIJAN         A-463-202
GEORGIA            A-463-302
KAZAKHSTAN         A-463-402
KYRGYZSTAN         A-463-502
MOLDOVA            A-464-102
TAJIKISTAN         A-464-202
TURKMENISTAN       A-464-302
UZBEKISTAN         A-464-402
6.  IF  THERE ARE  ANY QUESTIONS REGARDING THIS MATTER BY CUSTOMS
OFFICERS, THEY  SHOULD  CONTACT  THE  IMPORT SPECIALIST DIVISION,
OTHER AGENCY BRANCH (202-566-8651), OR SEND AN EMAIL TO ATTRIBUTE
"HQ  OAB".   THE  IMPORTING PUBLIC  AND  OTHER INTERESTED PARTIES
SHOULD CONTACT LARRY SULLIVAN  OF  THE  OFFICE  OF COUNTERVAILING
INVESTIGATIONS,   IMPORT   ADMINISTRATION,  INTERNATIONAL   TRADE
ADMINISTRATION,   U.S.   DEPARTMENT   OF   COMMERCE,   TELEPHONE:
THERE ARE NO RESTRICTIONS ON RELEASE OF THE ABOVE INFORMATION.
NANCY MCTIERNAN
